questions += [
  {"question_text":"What is Amazon DocumentDB?","options":["A document management service","A managed document database service compatible with MongoDB","A PDF processing service","A file storage service"],"correct_answer":"A managed document database service compatible with MongoDB","explanation":"Amazon DocumentDB is a fully managed document database service that is compatible with MongoDB. It supports MongoDB workloads and provides the scalability, durability, and security of a fully managed AWS service.","memory_technique":"DocumentDB = MongoDB managed by AWS. Same MongoDB API, no cluster management.","topic_area":"Technology","difficulty_level":2,"it_context_mapping":"DocumentDB replaces self-managed MongoDB clusters. It provides the same document database capabilities without managing replica sets, sharding, and patching."},
  {"question_text":"What is Amazon Keyspaces?","options":["A key management service","A managed Apache Cassandra-compatible database service","A key-value cache service","A secrets management service"],"correct_answer":"A managed Apache Cassandra-compatible database service","explanation":"Amazon Keyspaces is a scalable, highly available, and managed Apache Cassandra-compatible database service. You can run Cassandra workloads without managing servers or software.","memory_technique":"Keyspaces = Managed Cassandra. Same CQL (Cassandra Query Language), no cluster management.","topic_area":"Technology","difficulty_level":2,"it_context_mapping":"Keyspaces replaces self-managed Cassandra clusters. It provides the same wide-column database capabilities without managing nodes, compaction, and repairs."},
  {"question_text":"What is AWS App Runner?","options":["A mobile app testing service","A fully managed service for deploying containerised web applications without managing infrastructure","A CI/CD pipeline service","A serverless function service"],"correct_answer":"A fully managed service for deploying containerised web applications without managing infrastructure","explanation":"AWS App Runner is a fully managed service that makes it easy to deploy containerised web applications and APIs. You provide your container image or source code, and App Runner handles deployment, scaling, and load balancing.","memory_technique":"App Runner = Runs your app for you. Push code or container → it runs. Like Heroku on AWS.","topic_area":"Technology","difficulty_level":2,"it_context_mapping":"App Runner is equivalent to PaaS container services like Google Cloud Run or Azure Container Apps — fully managed container hosting without Kubernetes complexity."},
  {"question_text":"What is AWS Amplify?","options":["A sound amplification service","A set of tools and services for building full-stack web and mobile applications","A network amplification service","A data amplification service"],"correct_answer":"A set of tools and services for building full-stack web and mobile applications","explanation":"AWS Amplify provides a set of tools and services for building full-stack web and mobile applications. It includes hosting, authentication, APIs, storage, and CI/CD — all configured through a simple CLI or console.","memory_technique":"Amplify = Amplify your development speed. Full-stack toolkit for web/mobile apps — auth, API, hosting, all in one.","topic_area":"Technology","difficulty_level":2,"it_context_mapping":"Amplify is equivalent to Firebase (Google) or Supabase — a backend-as-a-service platform that provides common app features without building them from scratch."},
  {"question_text":"What is the purpose of AWS CloudWatch Container Insights?","options":["To monitor container images for vulnerabilities","To collect, aggregate, and summarise metrics and logs from containerised applications on ECS, EKS, and Kubernetes","To manage container registries","To deploy containers"],"correct_answer":"To collect, aggregate, and summarise metrics and logs from containerised applications on ECS, EKS, and Kubernetes","explanation":"CloudWatch Container Insights collects, aggregates, and summarises metrics and logs from containerised applications. It provides dashboards showing cluster, node, pod, and task-level performance metrics.","memory_technique":"Container Insights = X-ray vision for containers. See CPU, memory, and network for every pod, task, and node in your cluster.","topic_area":"Technology","difficulty_level":3,"it_context_mapping":"Container Insights is equivalent to container monitoring tools like Datadog or Prometheus+Grafana — providing visibility into container orchestration platforms."},
  {"question_text":"What is the purpose of AWS Proton?","options":["A particle physics simulation service","A fully managed service for deploying and managing container and serverless applications with standardised templates","A network protocol service","A database service"],"correct_answer":"A fully managed service for deploying and managing container and serverless applications with standardised templates","explanation":"AWS Proton is a fully managed delivery service for container and serverless applications. Platform teams define standardised infrastructure templates; developers deploy applications using those templates without needing infrastructure expertise.","memory_technique":"Proton = Platform engineering tool. Platform team creates templates; developers deploy from them. Standardised infrastructure delivery.","topic_area":"Technology","difficulty_level":3,"it_context_mapping":"Proton is equivalent to an internal developer platform (IDP) — platform teams define golden paths and developers self-serve infrastructure without needing to understand the underlying complexity."},
  {"question_text":"What is the purpose of Amazon Managed Grafana?","options":["A managed database service","A fully managed service for creating Grafana dashboards and visualisations for operational data","A graph database service","A network monitoring service"],"correct_answer":"A fully managed service for creating Grafana dashboards and visualisations for operational data","explanation":"Amazon Managed Grafana is a fully managed service for Grafana, the popular open-source analytics and visualisation platform. It integrates with CloudWatch, Prometheus, X-Ray, and other data sources for operational dashboards.","memory_technique":"Managed Grafana = Grafana without managing servers. Beautiful dashboards for your metrics — AWS handles the Grafana infrastructure.","topic_area":"Technology","difficulty_level":3,"it_context_mapping":"Managed Grafana replaces self-hosted Grafana instances. It provides the same visualisation capabilities without managing the Grafana server, database, and upgrades."},
  {"question_text":"What is the purpose of Amazon Managed Prometheus?","options":["A managed database service","A fully managed Prometheus-compatible monitoring service for container metrics","A managed message queue","A managed search service"],"correct_answer":"A fully managed Prometheus-compatible monitoring service for container metrics","explanation":"Amazon Managed Service for Prometheus is a Prometheus-compatible monitoring service for container metrics. It provides scalable, secure monitoring without managing Prometheus servers, storage, or high availability.","memory_technique":"Managed Prometheus = Prometheus without the ops. Same PromQL queries, same metrics format — AWS manages the infrastructure.","topic_area":"Technology","difficulty_level":3,"it_context_mapping":"Managed Prometheus replaces self-hosted Prometheus clusters. It provides the same time-series monitoring capabilities without managing storage, federation, and high availability."},
  {"question_text":"What is the purpose of AWS IoT Core?","options":["A service for managing IoT device hardware","A managed cloud service that lets connected devices interact with cloud applications and other devices securely","A service for manufacturing IoT devices","A service for selling IoT devices"],"correct_answer":"A managed cloud service that lets connected devices interact with cloud applications and other devices securely","explanation":"AWS IoT Core lets connected devices securely interact with cloud applications and other devices. It supports MQTT, HTTPS, and WebSocket protocols and can handle billions of messages.","memory_technique":"IoT Core = Cloud hub for IoT devices. Devices connect, send data, receive commands — all managed and secure.","topic_area":"Technology","difficulty_level":3,"it_context_mapping":"IoT Core replaces custom MQTT brokers and device management platforms. It provides managed device connectivity, authentication, and message routing at scale."},
  {"question_text":"What is the purpose of AWS Ground Station?","options":["A service for managing on-premises servers","A fully managed service for controlling satellite communications, processing satellite data, and scaling satellite operations","A service for ground-level network connectivity","A service for managing data center facilities"],"correct_answer":"A fully managed service for controlling satellite communications, processing satellite data, and scaling satellite operations","explanation":"AWS Ground Station is a fully managed service that lets you control satellite communications, process satellite data, and scale satellite operations without building or managing ground station infrastructure.","memory_technique":"Ground Station = Satellite dish as a service. Communicate with satellites without building your own ground infrastructure.","topic_area":"Technology","difficulty_level":3,"it_context_mapping":"Ground Station replaces the need to build and maintain physical satellite ground stations — providing satellite communication infrastructure on demand."},
  {"question_text":"What is the purpose of AWS Outposts Rack vs Outposts Server?","options":["They are the same","Outposts Rack is a full 42U rack for large deployments; Outposts Server is a 1U/2U server for smaller or space-constrained environments","Rack is for storage; Server is for compute","Server is larger than Rack"],"correct_answer":"Outposts Rack is a full 42U rack for large deployments; Outposts Server is a 1U/2U server for smaller or space-constrained environments","explanation":"Outposts Rack delivers a full 42U rack of AWS compute and storage for large on-premises deployments. Outposts Server provides a 1U or 2U server for smaller environments like retail stores, branch offices, or edge locations with limited space.","memory_technique":"Outposts Rack = Full rack (big). Outposts Server = Single server (small). Choose based on space and capacity needs.","topic_area":"Technology","difficulty_level":3,"it_context_mapping":"Outposts Rack is like a full server rack in a data center; Outposts Server is like a branch office server — different form factors for different deployment sizes."},
  {"question_text":"What is the purpose of AWS Local Zones?","options":["Zones for local development only","AWS infrastructure deployments that place compute, storage, and database services closer to large population centres for single-digit millisecond latency","Local backup zones","Zones for local testing"],"correct_answer":"AWS infrastructure deployments that place compute, storage, and database services closer to large population centres for single-digit millisecond latency","explanation":"AWS Local Zones are extensions of AWS Regions that place compute, storage, database, and other services closer to large population centres. They provide single-digit millisecond latency for applications that need to be near end users.","memory_technique":"Local Zones = AWS mini-regions in cities. Closer to users = lower latency. For real-time apps that need to be near a specific metro area.","topic_area":"Technology","difficulty_level":3,"it_context_mapping":"Local Zones are equivalent to edge data centers in major cities — providing low-latency compute closer to users than the nearest full AWS Region."},
  {"question_text":"What is the purpose of AWS Savings Plans purchase recommendations?","options":["To recommend which AWS services to use","To analyse usage patterns and recommend optimal Savings Plans commitments","To recommend security improvements","To recommend performance optimisations"],"correct_answer":"To analyse usage patterns and recommend optimal Savings Plans commitments","explanation":"AWS provides Savings Plans purchase recommendations in Cost Explorer based on your historical usage. They show the recommended hourly commitment, estimated savings, and estimated coverage for different term lengths and payment options.","memory_technique":"SP recommendations = AWS says 'based on your history, commit $X/hour to save Y%.' Data-driven purchasing advice.","topic_area":"Billing and Pricing","difficulty_level":3,"it_context_mapping":"SP recommendations are equivalent to procurement analysis — using historical consumption data to determine the optimal volume commitment for maximum discount."},
  {"question_text":"What is the purpose of AWS Cost Anomaly Detection monitors?","options":["To monitor EC2 performance","To define the scope of cost monitoring — by service, account, cost category, or cost allocation tag","To monitor security anomalies","To monitor network anomalies"],"correct_answer":"To define the scope of cost monitoring — by service, account, cost category, or cost allocation tag","explanation":"Cost Anomaly Detection monitors define what spending to watch. You can create monitors for individual services, linked accounts, cost categories, or cost allocation tags. Each monitor independently detects anomalies in its scope.","memory_technique":"Monitors = Scope of detection. One monitor per service, account, or tag. Each watches its own slice of spending for anomalies.","topic_area":"Billing and Pricing","difficulty_level":3,"it_context_mapping":"Monitors are equivalent to defining alert scopes in financial monitoring systems — watching specific cost centres or budget categories for unusual spending patterns."},
]

